10
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,830
They say there's a reason

11
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:05,000
behind everything
in this world.

12
00:02:06,790 --> 00:02:08,250
But, can you think of a reason

13
00:02:09,050 --> 00:02:10,670
behind what's going on here?

14
00:02:12,510 --> 00:02:14,680
This place is beyond reason.

15
00:02:15,590 --> 00:02:16,850
This is Bakrapur.

16
00:02:33,530 --> 00:02:34,740
O' Lord!

17
00:02:40,330 --> 00:02:42,910
May the Lord bless you
with his grace.

18
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:44,460
How are you?

19
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:51,250
May the Lord bless you
with his grace.

20
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:02,270
May the Lord bless you
with his grace.

21
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:04,600
How is business?
- Good.

22
00:03:06,850 --> 00:03:07,900
My Lord!

23
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:13,570
May the Lord bless you
with his grace.

24
00:03:18,030 --> 00:03:19,070
O' Lord!

25
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:22,830
Don't hoard.
Share what you have.

26
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,330
You can't take it to your grave.

27
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:28,750
You brought nothing.
You'll take back nothing.

28
00:03:29,580 --> 00:03:30,880
Right?
Let's drink to it.

29
00:03:37,180 --> 00:03:38,720
May the Lord bless you!

30
00:03:43,310 --> 00:03:44,720
Not a penny more.

31
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:46,980
But the deal was for 3000!

32
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:49,060
3000 bucks for incense?

33
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:52,070
No. I was talking
about Shahrukh.

34
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:56,320
Suraiyya finalized
everything with Mr. Usman.

35
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,650
Fine, take a seat.

36
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,200
Come on, boy.

37
00:04:28,230 --> 00:04:29,770
Zulfi, are you dreaming again?

38
00:04:31,060 --> 00:04:32,940
Memorize the entire
lesson by tomorrow.

39
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,520
Yes, teacher.

40
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:35,940
Concentrate.

41
00:04:40,110 --> 00:04:42,700
No more mischief!
Keep studying..

42
00:04:56,710 --> 00:04:58,010
Suraiyya!

43
00:04:58,630 --> 00:04:59,760
Suraiyya!

44
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:04,260
Greetings, Ms. Nooran.
- Greetings.

45
00:05:05,180 --> 00:05:06,770
I was on my way to the city.

46
00:05:07,270 --> 00:05:08,850
Did you arrange for the money?

47
00:05:09,020 --> 00:05:12,440
He left for the city just this
morning, along with his uncle.

48
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,400
I will somehow get the
money to you by evening.

49
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:17,400
I guess you aren't
tired of making excuses.

50
00:05:17,530 --> 00:05:19,690
But I am tired of
listening to them.

51
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,620
I bought imported
shoes for myself.

52
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:34,500
I'll elope with you in a trice.

53
00:05:35,090 --> 00:05:36,290
I see.
- What?

54
00:05:36,590 --> 00:05:38,340
I've things to do here.

55
00:05:39,090 --> 00:05:40,130
That's why I say

56
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:42,130
talk to your father.

57
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:44,510
I'll treat you
like a movie star.

58
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:47,430
Star!

59
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,470
This cheap mobile
that you bought me

60
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,430
can't even take
decent pictures.

61
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,690
Forget the mobile.

62
00:05:52,940 --> 00:05:54,100
I'll bring you a
laptop this time.

63
00:05:54,230 --> 00:05:55,810
The big one.
One with a camera.

64
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:57,610
Listen.
- What?

65
00:05:57,860 --> 00:05:58,900
Naaz.

66
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:00,650
How about a kiss?

67
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:03,360
Don't laugh.

68
00:06:03,490 --> 00:06:04,820
Have you seen yourself
in the mirror?

69
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:07,910
Asking for a kiss!
- I have. I look nice.

70
00:06:08,030 --> 00:06:11,870
Naaz. What are you doing?
- Who was that?

71
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:14,080
Listen, I need to get going.

72
00:06:14,210 --> 00:06:15,460
I am not done yet.

73
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:17,750
Are you still there?
- Coming, mother.

74
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,380
Cut your crap, I have to go.

75
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:22,340
Mother's here. Goodbye.
- Naaz..

76
00:06:22,670 --> 00:06:25,090
Why don't you all just kill me?

77
00:06:26,050 --> 00:06:27,680
I was working, mother.

78
00:06:28,470 --> 00:06:30,970
I hope you didn't get blisters.

79
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,600
An incompetent husband

80
00:06:32,730 --> 00:06:33,690
and two good-for-nothing
children.

81
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:35,560
There's just no end
to my problems.

82
00:06:35,850 --> 00:06:39,230
What the heck is that?
- Mother, must be a bee..

83
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,400
Please go inside,
I'll be with you.

84
00:06:40,530 --> 00:06:42,030
Come soon.
- Yes, mother.

85
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:44,820
Naaz!

86
00:06:57,580 --> 00:06:58,790
Zulfi!

87
00:07:01,670 --> 00:07:02,710
Zulfi!

88
00:07:07,090 --> 00:07:08,050
Hey, hot shot!

89
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:12,770
What's wrong with you?

90
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:17,270
Zulfi!

91
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:19,940
Why so sad?

92
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:23,190
Say something.
- It's nothing, Mr. Jaffer.

93
00:07:24,150 --> 00:07:25,450
Nothing?

94
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:28,740
Then why do you look
like a sacrificial lamb?

95
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,040
Zulfi!

96
00:07:39,580 --> 00:07:41,380
I was looking for you.

97
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:46,300
Wait.

98
00:07:47,340 --> 00:07:48,390
Get on my bike.

99
00:07:51,050 --> 00:07:54,810
How can a man be so stupid?

100
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,690
Suraiyya. Is it my fault

101
00:07:57,810 --> 00:08:00,270
that Usman's mother-in-law
broke her back?

102
00:08:00,610 --> 00:08:03,650
No, it's entirely my fault!

103
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:05,440
It's my father's fault!

104
00:08:05,570 --> 00:08:09,030
For getting me married
to a penniless man.

105
00:08:09,740 --> 00:08:11,660
And what was the point
of you going along?

106
00:08:11,780 --> 00:08:14,580
You two are just useless.

107
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:16,960
Teach her some manners.

108
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:18,790
If she continues
yelling this way

109
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,250
we'll soon rot in inferno.

110
00:08:20,380 --> 00:08:24,670
Right. Just sit here and rant
about heaven and inferno.

111
00:08:25,170 --> 00:08:26,720
A woman has to do the chores

112
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,880
as well as amass money
by selling eggs and hens.

113
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:31,760
The men of this family,
lazy to the core!

114
00:08:31,970 --> 00:08:34,640
Arrange for the money somehow.

115
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,930
Otherwise, I'm going
back to my mother's.

116
00:08:37,060 --> 00:08:39,060
I won't stay here
a minute longer.

117
00:08:53,490 --> 00:08:54,660
Come in, Mr. Munna.

118
00:08:54,780 --> 00:08:55,910
I am free.
Come in.

119
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:57,370
I want to style my hair.
Is Mr. Jaffer in?

120
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:00,080
Greetings.
- See you later.

121
00:09:00,210 --> 00:09:01,960
Go on in.
- Take a seat.

122
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:05,840
Ever since you returned from the
city, business has been slow.

123
00:09:06,210 --> 00:09:07,550
Everyone asks for Jaffer.

124
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:08,720
And for free.

125
00:09:10,130 --> 00:09:12,760
Father, why be sad?

126
00:09:13,050 --> 00:09:15,140
They come here
because they've faith in me

127
00:09:15,260 --> 00:09:17,560
as I've learnt
new techniques.

128
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,350
How can I charge them money?

129
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,100
In fact,
I should be paying them.

130
00:09:21,230 --> 00:09:23,060
I'm getting a chance to practice.
Look at this new style.

131
00:09:23,190 --> 00:09:25,440
Shall I teach you?
- Shut up! What faith?

132
00:09:25,570 --> 00:09:29,110
A beggar asking for alms
is happy with what he gets.

133
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,200
They are here for freebies.
- Father.

134
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,530
Yes.
- Chill, dude.

135
00:09:34,660 --> 00:09:36,580
How about I thrash you..
- No, no, remain seated.

136
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:47,590
Haven't you finished yet?

137
00:09:48,710 --> 00:09:50,470
Just a little longer.

138
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:53,640
I see.
- Yes.

139
00:09:54,430 --> 00:09:55,850
What are you doing here?

140
00:09:55,970 --> 00:09:58,220
I was running an errand
for my mother.

141
00:09:59,310 --> 00:10:02,100
You know,
I soaked henna yesterday.

142
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:05,560
Come tomorrow,
and we'll apply it together.

143
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:09,280
And, is everything okay?

144
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:15,700
Naaz.

145
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:18,540
What are you doing here?

146
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:21,540
Come on, go home.
Your mother's looking for you.

147
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,130
Didn't you hear it?

148
00:10:25,460 --> 00:10:26,500
Go home.

149
00:10:28,170 --> 00:10:31,010
I am going, there's no need to yell.

150
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:33,050
Go on. Go home.

151
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,590
Did he have to drop in now?

152
00:10:37,010 --> 00:10:38,470
Greetings.
- Greetings.

153
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,680
No, no.. Leave.

154
00:10:41,220 --> 00:10:43,730
Majid,
you were really brave today.

155
00:10:44,850 --> 00:10:45,850
Give me a smoke.

156
00:10:46,310 --> 00:10:50,860
Zulfi. What do we do
with your hair today?

157
00:10:51,110 --> 00:10:52,780
What style would you like?

158
00:10:53,650 --> 00:10:55,740
Aamir? Salman?

159
00:10:56,030 --> 00:11:00,740
Or Shahrukh.
- The children these days..

160
00:11:00,950 --> 00:11:04,710
What can a poor mother
do all alone?

161
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:06,750
Majid wants to get romantic.

162
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,840
But his wife's just
not playing along.

163
00:11:09,630 --> 00:11:10,630
Go ahead, make fun of me.

164
00:11:11,090 --> 00:11:12,880
Can't help it when
I'm ill-fated.

165
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:15,430
Are you Majid?

166
00:11:17,090 --> 00:11:18,850
Yes. Is something wrong?

167
00:11:19,510 --> 00:11:20,640
Is Suraiyya home?

168
00:11:22,180 --> 00:11:24,430
Suraiyya..
She is.

169
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:26,140
Let's go.

170
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:34,070
Mother.
- Yes.

171
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,490
Mother. They are here!
- Who?

172
00:11:38,950 --> 00:11:41,120
Them! - Them?
- Yes.

173
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:45,910
Your father didn't exactly
leave behind a fortune!

174
00:11:46,210 --> 00:11:47,830
Tell them I'm not at home.
Go on.

175
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,540
But, mother.
They met father on the way.

176
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:52,840
Oh God! I'm tired of this man!

177
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,130
Go on, I'm coming.

178
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:57,930
Yes.

179
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:02,430
Is everyone here?

180
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:04,600
Start collecting.
Shakuntala!

181
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:07,520
Vidyavati.

182
00:12:08,850 --> 00:12:09,900
Saraswati.

183
00:12:10,770 --> 00:12:13,150
I hope you're making
sure their payment's right.

184
00:12:13,530 --> 00:12:14,530
Mallika.

185
00:12:15,190 --> 00:12:17,650
Yes.
- Is it all there?

186
00:12:22,530 --> 00:12:24,120
Greetings, ma'am.
- I see.

187
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,790
So, you're finally here.

188
00:12:26,870 --> 00:12:28,120
That's not it, ma'am.

189
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,460
Why wouldn't I come to meet you?

190
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,460
I won't be fooled
by you anymore.

191
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:36,670
And your leader, Nooran..

192
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:39,550
She's been taking your side.
- No, ma'am.

193
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:43,260
I visit her on your behalf.

194
00:12:43,850 --> 00:12:45,680
Ma'am, my circumstances
are such that..

195
00:12:46,060 --> 00:12:49,020
It's no secret, everyone
knows about my situation.

196
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:53,310
Zulfi's father's aunt, who
lives in Sultanpur, fell ill.

197
00:12:53,690 --> 00:12:55,650
I wonder what sort of
an outbreak it was

198
00:12:55,820 --> 00:12:57,440
and half my poultry
succumbed to it.

199
00:12:57,570 --> 00:12:59,240
And then..
- Stop.

200
00:12:59,530 --> 00:13:00,610
In the last three months

201
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:03,530
you haven't paid the
loan or the interest.

202
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:06,830
Ma'am, try to understand.
I swear on my child.

203
00:13:06,950 --> 00:13:08,580
I'm not lying.

204
00:13:08,710 --> 00:13:10,580
The circumstances..
Just give me a little more time!

205
00:13:10,710 --> 00:13:15,210
Look, Suraiyya. All these
women have repaid their loan.

206
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:18,970
If you don't repay
the money in a week

207
00:13:19,130 --> 00:13:21,800
I will stop everyone's
loan in this group.

208
00:13:21,930 --> 00:13:23,140
No one will get anything.

209
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:27,600
See that. Helping you has
landed all of us in trouble.

210
00:13:28,770 --> 00:13:30,350
What do I say?

211
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:33,440
I was honestly coming
to the office to pay you.

212
00:13:33,650 --> 00:13:35,610
But just then, Mr. Usman's

213
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:37,110
mother-in-law broke her back.

214
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:38,740
We're in a lot of trouble..

215
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:40,110
You should've thought
about it before.

216
00:13:40,570 --> 00:13:42,740
I explained the rules
in the beginning.

217
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:45,120
Didn't I?
- Yes.

218
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:50,040
Look, Suraiyya.
If you don't return the money

219
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:53,420
in a week, then be ready
to face legal procedures.

220
00:13:53,710 --> 00:13:55,000
Everyone!

221
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:57,710
Let's go!

222
00:14:08,010 --> 00:14:12,850
Hocus-Pocus!
Abracadabra!

223
00:14:13,690 --> 00:14:14,730
Run away!

224
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,560
Leave this kid alone!

225
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:18,360
Go!

226
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:20,860
Go away!

227
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:26,530
Ma'am, the kid's being
haunted by a spirit.

228
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:28,660
But don't you worry.

229
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,580
I've chanted a strong mantra

230
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,750
and got rid of it.

231
00:14:33,460 --> 00:14:34,420
Here.

232
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:36,460
Make him wear this
in the morning, after bath.

233
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:39,090
Everything will be okay.
May the Lord bless you!

234
00:14:45,010 --> 00:14:46,050
What's wrong?

235
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:48,760
Why are you upset?

236
00:14:49,180 --> 00:14:50,850
Have you eaten
or are you fasting?

237
00:14:51,020 --> 00:14:53,180
No..
Why would he fast?

238
00:14:53,940 --> 00:14:56,230
All the villagers
are humiliating me.

239
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:58,520
And all you two care
about is stuffing your mouths.

240
00:14:59,150 --> 00:15:00,940
I want the money
before Thursday..

241
00:15:01,110 --> 00:15:02,440
Otherwise, I won't
stay here a moment.

242
00:15:02,690 --> 00:15:03,650
Spare me!

243
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:05,780
How can we get
the money so soon?

244
00:15:05,950 --> 00:15:07,700
Who will lend us the money,
uncle?

245
00:15:07,820 --> 00:15:09,830
Of course.
Who will lend you the money?

246
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:12,410
The only one who could,
gave you his daughter instead.

247
00:15:13,710 --> 00:15:16,460
Mother, I am hungry.
- Why did you bring him inside?

248
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:18,670
Naaz, take him outside.
- Come in.

249
00:15:23,550 --> 00:15:25,050
Don't worry, I know a way.

250
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,640
What is it, uncle?
Tell me.

251
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,600
Don't worry,
we'll get the money.

252
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,470
Where will we get it from?

253
00:15:31,890 --> 00:15:33,480
Is there a lottery running
for mendicants now?

254
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,480
Stop taunting me.

255
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,360
I was talking about Shahrukh.
- Shahrukh?

256
00:15:39,810 --> 00:15:41,520
I can never make
sense of what you say.

257
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:44,280
The animal fair of Malshapur
is quite popular.

258
00:15:44,530 --> 00:15:45,950
We'll take Shahrukh there.

259
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,820
Many buyers come there.

260
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:49,370
We'll get a good price.

261
00:15:49,620 --> 00:15:52,160
Usman offered better
than that, for sure.

262
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:55,410
You're right, uncle.

263
00:16:32,870 --> 00:16:35,120
Zulfi, catch the ball.

264
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:39,870
Zulfi. Could you not have
caught the ball?

265
00:17:09,450 --> 00:17:11,030
Oh God!

266
00:17:14,740 --> 00:17:17,080
The Lord had
answered my prayers

267
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,790
and blessed me with a son.

268
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:20,960
And now, he's gone as well.

269
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:26,960
Uncle. I looked everywhere,
but Zulfi's nowhere.

270
00:17:27,340 --> 00:17:29,720
Oh God! My son.

271
00:17:30,220 --> 00:17:33,890
He's just a child.
Where can he possibly go?

272
00:17:34,140 --> 00:17:37,310
He didn't go alone,
he took Shahrukh along.

273
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:38,770
What were you doing?

274
00:17:39,890 --> 00:17:41,600
Uncle, they left quietly.

275
00:17:41,730 --> 00:17:44,400
Even that animal
didn't make a sound.

276
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:48,860
Stop crying like a girl!

277
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:51,070
My son!

278
00:17:52,740 --> 00:17:54,700
I told you not to call.

279
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,950
Everyone's so worried.

280
00:17:57,290 --> 00:17:59,700
Sweetheart, I'm worried too.
In your love.

281
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:02,500
Listen. I had a wonderful
dream this morning.

282
00:18:03,710 --> 00:18:05,630
You and me, by the seaside.

283
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:06,840
It was beautiful.

284
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:11,260
Naaz..
Naaz. Why are you crying?

285
00:18:11,380 --> 00:18:14,680
What's the matter. - Zulfi ran away
from home.. - What?

286
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:17,220
What are you saying?
When did this happen?

287
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:19,100
And, with Shahrukh.

288
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:47,960
Hey!

289
00:18:51,170 --> 00:18:52,260
Wonderful.

290
00:18:52,510 --> 00:18:54,300
Everyone's worried back home

291
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:56,890
while you two
are having a ball.

292
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:58,220
And, with biscuits.

293
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:00,470
I knew this is where
I would find you.

294
00:19:01,060 --> 00:19:04,100
You know,
when father would beat me

295
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:07,230
I too would hide here.

296
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:09,520
It's a nice place, right?

297
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:13,190
Listen, let's go home.

298
00:19:13,490 --> 00:19:14,900
No, I don't want to go home.

299
00:19:15,610 --> 00:19:18,320
Where else do you want to go?
- Take us to the city.

300
00:19:18,450 --> 00:19:19,830
We will work with you too.

301
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:22,290
Come along,
and bring Shahrukh too.

302
00:19:22,910 --> 00:19:25,250
He will make for a great barber.

303
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:27,580
Shahrukh that is..
Let's go.

304
00:19:27,710 --> 00:19:29,130
We'll go to the city later,
let's now go home.

305
00:19:29,250 --> 00:19:31,340
Can't we stay here until Sunday?

306
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:33,010
What's on Sunday?

307
00:19:33,470 --> 00:19:37,300
They're taking Shahrukh
to the Malshapur fair that day.

308
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:41,310
So, you want to hide
here till Sunday? - Yes.

309
00:19:41,930 --> 00:19:43,060
Great.

310
00:19:44,060 --> 00:19:45,600
What will you do next Sunday?

311
00:19:45,730 --> 00:19:49,440
The fair's just once a month.
- You're smart.

312
00:19:49,610 --> 00:19:51,110
What will you do next month?

313
00:19:55,110 --> 00:19:56,650
I don't know, Mr. Jaffer!

314
00:19:56,860 --> 00:19:58,660
Just take us along.

315
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,660
I don't know, Mr. Jaffer.

316
00:20:01,490 --> 00:20:03,120
Come along with me.

317
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:05,080
You've my word
that nothing will go wrong.

318
00:20:05,210 --> 00:20:07,790
We'll go to the city too
tagging Shahrukh and you along.

319
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:09,630
Let's go home now.
- Why did you run away?

320
00:20:09,830 --> 00:20:11,710
Do you know how worried we were?

321
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:16,630
If you ever do it again,
I'll break your limbs.

322
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:17,800
That's great, ma'am.

323
00:20:18,010 --> 00:20:20,140
That's a nice way
to teach him a lesson.

324
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:23,310
Break his legs.
- I don't like saying it either.

325
00:20:24,020 --> 00:20:26,640
A child never understands
a mother's heart.

326
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:31,110
May the Lord bless you
with progress in your work.

327
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:34,440
Work's good, ma'am.

328
00:20:34,690 --> 00:20:37,900
Just bless me so that
I find a nice bride.

329
00:20:38,030 --> 00:20:40,030
That's it.
- Of course.

330
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:44,040
Any girl would be
fortunate to marry you.

331
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,290
I see.

332
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:48,160
So, sir..

333
00:20:48,290 --> 00:20:51,580
Are you sure about
the Malshapur fair?

334
00:20:52,250 --> 00:20:54,670
Yes, I..
- There's no other choice.

335
00:20:55,170 --> 00:20:57,130
These children have
never had to starve

336
00:20:57,260 --> 00:20:59,470
so, they will never
understand our condition.

337
00:21:01,050 --> 00:21:03,010
They will have to understand,
ma'am.

338
00:21:12,770 --> 00:21:16,190
The food's begging to be eaten.

339
00:21:16,690 --> 00:21:18,490
But, the boy's still stubborn.

340
00:21:21,950 --> 00:21:24,950
Fine. You want to starve,
don't you? Then go ahead.

341
00:21:30,670 --> 00:21:33,880
Zulfi. Don't infuriate me.

342
00:21:34,670 --> 00:21:37,840
Mother. Leave him alone.
I'll console him.

343
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:39,670
Oh my!

344
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:42,300
You never cared so much
about your mother before.

345
00:21:43,390 --> 00:21:44,430
Why, mother?

346
00:21:45,310 --> 00:21:48,140
Can't I console him?
He's my brother after all.

347
00:21:48,270 --> 00:21:49,810
Yes, he is.

348
00:21:49,980 --> 00:21:51,850
I am the only enemy
in this house.

349
00:21:52,310 --> 00:21:55,110
You two can do anything
you want to. Just spare me.

350
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:56,780
I don't have the will anymore.

351
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,530
Mother's just impossible!

352
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:04,490
Zulfi. Get up.

353
00:22:04,740 --> 00:22:06,790
Come with your sister.
- No. I don't want to go.

354
00:22:07,370 --> 00:22:09,160
Hear me out.

355
00:22:09,290 --> 00:22:12,370
Let's go sit outside.
- Leave me alone, sister.

356
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:15,790
I said, don't be stubborn.

357
00:22:17,130 --> 00:22:19,590
Come along. Come on..

358
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:21,340
Come on.

359
00:22:25,140 --> 00:22:27,310
Mother's always scolding him.

360
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:29,470
And he isn't eating either.

361
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,770
Talk to him.

362
00:22:31,180 --> 00:22:33,270
Who is it?
- Here.

363
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:36,270
Zulfi.
- Mr. Jaffer!

364
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:38,190
So, why aren't you eating?

365
00:22:38,780 --> 00:22:40,650
No, I don't want to eat?

366
00:22:40,780 --> 00:22:41,820
Why?

367
00:22:42,490 --> 00:22:45,490
They are taking Shahrukh away.

368
00:22:45,950 --> 00:22:47,370
Don't you want to save him?

369
00:22:47,580 --> 00:22:48,740
Yes.

370
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:50,330
Then do as I say.

371
00:22:50,540 --> 00:22:52,910
Go inside and finish your meal.

372
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:55,000
And come, meet me an hour later..

373
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:59,550
At the old fort,
along with Shahrukh.

374
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:02,090
And, don't tell anyone about it.
Understood?

375
00:23:48,850 --> 00:23:50,390
Do you attend school?

376
00:23:50,970 --> 00:23:52,100
Yes.

377
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:53,640
Why?

378
00:23:57,190 --> 00:23:58,730
Read this aloud.

379
00:24:01,820 --> 00:24:02,780
What's written..

380
00:24:03,740 --> 00:24:06,030
Alif..

381
00:24:07,860 --> 00:24:09,160
Laam..

382
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:10,950
Zulfi!

383
00:24:11,490 --> 00:24:13,500
Are you going to take
that long to read it?

384
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:16,210
Tell me now.
What's written in it?

385
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:18,880
Lord!

386
00:24:19,250 --> 00:24:21,000
It says Lord.

387
00:24:21,420 --> 00:24:22,670
That's it.

388
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:27,590
Now,
only Lord can save Shahrukh.

389
00:24:29,970 --> 00:24:31,100
How?

390
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:35,520
Like this.

391
00:24:54,620 --> 00:25:00,000
"A mighty goat escorted
by two courtiers."

392
00:25:01,080 --> 00:25:05,340
"A mighty goat escorted
by two courtiers."

393
00:25:05,550 --> 00:25:13,560
"Appreciate the irony.
Indulge in the ruckus.."

394
00:25:22,230 --> 00:25:26,940
"Be it the household merchandise,
the prices have gone sky high."

395
00:25:28,030 --> 00:25:30,570
He won't even give 10 kilos of meat.
What are you saying?

396
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:33,620
Nothing less than 4500..
- That's too much.

397
00:25:33,740 --> 00:25:35,740
2500 is all we can give.
2500 is too less.

398
00:25:36,790 --> 00:25:38,500
Go find someone else.

399
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:52,760
11,000!
- 11,000!

400
00:25:52,930 --> 00:25:55,100
How about 3000?
4000 is too much!

401
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:56,810
That's not possible.

402
00:26:00,940 --> 00:26:02,690
It's a fine goat.
Take a look.

403
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:05,320
How much?

404
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:06,900
How much?
- 5000!

405
00:26:07,030 --> 00:26:08,820
Quote reasonably!

406
00:26:08,940 --> 00:26:11,150
He's stuck at 5000!

407
00:26:11,910 --> 00:26:13,570
How much did you offer?
- Leave him.

408
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:15,700
How much did you offer?
- 2500.

409
00:26:16,030 --> 00:26:17,580
Let's settle for 3500.
That's it.

410
00:26:17,700 --> 00:26:19,950
Give me at least 4000.
- No, 4000 is too much.

411
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:21,460
Hear me out!

412
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:24,670
Just 500 more.
We've brought him from far.

413
00:26:24,790 --> 00:26:27,500
Even I have to go a long way.

414
00:26:27,630 --> 00:26:28,960
Let's settle for 3500.
That's it.

415
00:26:29,090 --> 00:26:30,220
Fine. How much are
you willing to offer?

416
00:26:30,340 --> 00:26:32,220
3500, that's it. Nothing more.

417
00:26:32,340 --> 00:26:33,470
Greetings, sir.

418
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:35,930
Greetings, lad.
What brings you here?

419
00:26:36,050 --> 00:26:37,100
Nothing, sir.

420
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:40,640
A friend of mine from the city,
lives here.

421
00:26:40,770 --> 00:26:41,850
So I came here with him.

422
00:26:41,980 --> 00:26:43,140
That's good, lad.

423
00:26:43,350 --> 00:26:46,110
How are you?
How are you, Shahrukh?

424
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:48,400
So, you're leaving us
today, right?

425
00:26:48,690 --> 00:26:52,320
Fine, hand over the rope to me.
I've got to leave.

426
00:26:52,530 --> 00:26:54,110
Just 500 more.

427
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:56,910
I'm offering you
a reasonable price.

428
00:26:57,030 --> 00:26:59,040
Okay, like you say.

429
00:26:59,620 --> 00:27:00,950
Sir.

430
00:27:01,330 --> 00:27:02,500
How much did you sell him for?

431
00:27:02,830 --> 00:27:06,420
3500. He's sold, at least.

432
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:08,590
What do you mean?

433
00:27:09,460 --> 00:27:12,670
You sold an animal worth
3 to 4 lakhs for few thousands.

434
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:15,720
3 lakhs?
- He's a prankster.

435
00:27:15,930 --> 00:27:18,640
Always playing pranks.
- I see.

436
00:27:18,760 --> 00:27:20,100
Don't listen to him.

437
00:27:20,220 --> 00:27:22,100
He's not covered with gold.
- Right.

438
00:27:22,430 --> 00:27:24,020
He's better than that,
sir.

439
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:25,940
He's blessed with
the grace of the Lord.

440
00:27:26,230 --> 00:27:27,310
Don't joke about this.

441
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:29,860
What? What are you saying?

442
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:31,690
Be clear, what are you saying?

443
00:27:32,490 --> 00:27:34,280
You're a mendicant.

444
00:27:35,820 --> 00:27:37,950
How could you miss this?
- What?

445
00:27:38,410 --> 00:27:40,330
Look here. Carefully.
Here.

446
00:27:40,740 --> 00:27:43,330
This. Take a good look.

447
00:27:44,370 --> 00:27:45,870
Look at the crescent shape.

448
00:27:47,330 --> 00:27:49,340
Have you seen the
Mecca-Medina calendar?

449
00:27:49,590 --> 00:27:50,630
You must have.

450
00:27:50,750 --> 00:27:53,300
The crescent shining,
on top of the dome.

451
00:27:53,470 --> 00:27:54,760
It's the same thing.

452
00:27:58,090 --> 00:28:00,430
You're a wise man.

453
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:01,680
And you didn't see it either.

454
00:28:01,970 --> 00:28:04,020
You didn't go on Haj, but
you've a world of experience.

455
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:05,560
Don't you?

456
00:28:06,730 --> 00:28:08,940
It's true.
- Yes.

457
00:28:10,570 --> 00:28:12,940
Child, it says Lord.

458
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:18,110
Hail the Lord!
My service has been accepted.

459
00:28:18,700 --> 00:28:20,330
He's an angel, child.

460
00:28:20,450 --> 00:28:22,450
Don't sell it.
- This is no ordinary goat!

461
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:23,950
I don't care.

462
00:28:24,450 --> 00:28:27,040
Just handover the animal to me.
I'll be on my way.

463
00:28:28,460 --> 00:28:30,380
Don't call him an animal.

464
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:31,960
He's an angel.
Apologize to him.

465
00:28:32,090 --> 00:28:33,250
We didn't take any
money from you.

466
00:28:33,380 --> 00:28:35,380
So, I am not refusing to pay.
Take it.

467
00:28:35,590 --> 00:28:36,720
Didn't we make a deal?

468
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:40,050
Look.
My nephew's not so wise.

469
00:28:40,220 --> 00:28:42,390
Look. We don't want to sell it.
Just leave. - Leave..

470
00:28:43,720 --> 00:28:46,100
But, uncle..
- Dear, didn't you see that?

471
00:28:46,230 --> 00:28:48,060
It's Lord written on him.

472
00:28:48,190 --> 00:28:49,190
We cannot sell him.

473
00:28:49,650 --> 00:28:51,900
But, uncle,
what will we tell Suraiyya?

474
00:28:52,070 --> 00:28:54,150
We cannot set foot in
the house without the money.

475
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:55,610
Henpecked husband!

476
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:57,570
Don't you understand
what Jaffer's saying?

477
00:28:57,700 --> 00:28:59,700
Lord is written on him.
- Yes.

478
00:28:59,950 --> 00:29:02,490
And, a Sheikh from Saudi

479
00:29:02,910 --> 00:29:05,290
paid 52 lakhs
for a similar goat.

480
00:29:05,450 --> 00:29:06,500
52 lakhs!

481
00:29:06,790 --> 00:29:08,960
52 lakhs.
- 52 lakhs?

482
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,830
He took it home on an airplane.

483
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:11,960
Airplane?

484
00:29:12,380 --> 00:29:13,380
Of course.

485
00:29:13,550 --> 00:29:15,590
It requires special permission
from the government.

486
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:17,220
But, how do you know?

487
00:29:17,340 --> 00:29:18,840
I read the newspaper.

488
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:20,720
And I can show you
the news as well.

489
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:21,890
Even the kids from
Delhi's Jamma Masjid area

490
00:29:22,010 --> 00:29:24,890
know about it.
Do you want to read it?

491
00:29:25,020 --> 00:29:27,520
Child, even I've heard
the Jamma Masjid story.

492
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:29,850
Indeed.
- Let's take him back.

493
00:29:29,980 --> 00:29:31,150
He's been blessed
by the Lord!

494
00:29:32,310 --> 00:29:35,780
How could I trust that man?
He's good for nothing.

495
00:29:36,650 --> 00:29:40,530
I wonder how father spent
so many years with you.

496
00:29:40,660 --> 00:29:42,700
Yes. We'll see.

497
00:29:42,910 --> 00:29:45,330
How your husband tolerates you!

498
00:29:50,670 --> 00:29:53,380
Mother. Father's back.

499
00:29:56,460 --> 00:29:57,550
Didn't I tell you?

500
00:29:57,710 --> 00:29:59,880
This man isn't
capable of anything.

501
00:30:00,010 --> 00:30:02,390
Stop.
Stop right there.

502
00:30:02,550 --> 00:30:03,930
Listen. Listen to me..

503
00:30:04,050 --> 00:30:05,510
Why don't you try
telling our creditors?

504
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:07,770
Maybe, they will listen to you.

505
00:30:07,970 --> 00:30:10,480
I'm trying to speak.
Let me speak!

506
00:30:12,020 --> 00:30:14,940
Look, dear.
Shahrukh' s no ordinary goat.

507
00:30:15,150 --> 00:30:17,190
He's blessed by the Lord!
He's special.

508
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:18,400
He's our golden goose.

509
00:30:18,570 --> 00:30:20,530
Are you two drunk?

510
00:30:21,070 --> 00:30:22,530
You could've brought
me some poison.

511
00:30:22,740 --> 00:30:24,450
God forbid.
Explain it to her.

512
00:30:24,910 --> 00:30:27,040
Suraiyya.. You tell her.

513
00:30:29,540 --> 00:30:30,870
He's right, ma'am.

514
00:30:31,750 --> 00:30:35,500
Jaffer says Shahrukh' s
not worth a few thousands

515
00:30:35,710 --> 00:30:37,420
but he's worth millions.

516
00:30:37,750 --> 00:30:39,880
And,
if we can find an Arab merchant

517
00:30:40,050 --> 00:30:41,840
he will definitely
pay millions for him.

518
00:30:41,970 --> 00:30:44,390
And, the story about 52 lakhs is
famous in Jamma Masjid. - Right.

519
00:30:44,510 --> 00:30:45,890
Even the kids know about it.
Right?

520
00:30:46,010 --> 00:30:47,060
I see.

521
00:30:47,180 --> 00:30:48,260
Tell her.
